-4 via xAI, Gemini 2.5 Flash Lite Preview, and UI improvements including /clear confirmation and /undo formatting enhancements.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"card-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"tag\">AI Coding Tool</span>\n                        <span>📅 2026-02-23</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"quote feedback-positive\">\n                        \"GPT-5 achieved 88% accuracy on Aider Polyglot benchmark, vs GPT-4o's 25.8%\"\n                        <span class=\"quote-source\">- Benchmark report</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"card\">\n                    <div class=\"card-title\">\n                        Cursor Background Agents in Slack\n                        <span class=\"badge badge-feature\">FEATURE</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"card-description\">\n                        Released Background Agents integration with Slack, allowing users to launch agents directly from Slack by mentioning @Cursor. Agents can read threads, understand context, and create PRs without leaving the conversation.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"card-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"tag\">IDE Integration</span>\n                        <span>📅 2026-02-19</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"quote feedback-positive\">\n                        \"这就是编程的未来\" (This is the future of programming)\n                        <span class=\"quote-source\">- User feedback</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"quote feedback-negative\">\n                        \"I can't imagine letting AI run on its own and finding a pile of garbage later\"\n                        <span class=\"quote-source\">- Skeptical user</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"card\">\n                    <div class=\"card-title\">\n                        Gemini CLI v0.29.0\n                        <span class=\"badge badge-release\">RELEASE</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"card-description\">\n                        Weekly updates continue with support for Gemini 3 Pro and Flash models with enhanced reasoning and coding capabilities.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"card-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"tag\">CLI Tool</span>\n                        <span>📅 2026-02-19</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"card\">\n                    <div class=\"card-title\">\n                        GitHub Copilot Agent Technology\n                        <span class=\"badge badge-feature\">FEATURE</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"card-description\">\n                        Integrated full agent technology with autonomous code iteration, Copilot Edits for multi-file editing, image upload support for code generation from visuals, and Next Edit Suggestions.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"card-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"tag\">IDE Integration</span>\n                        <span>📅 2026-02-18</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"card\">\n                    <div class=\"card-title\">\n                        GitHub Copilot Claude Sonnet 4.6\n                        <span class=\"badge badge-feature\">FEATURE</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"card-description\">\n                        Integrated Anthropic's Claude Sonnet 4.6 model, excelling at complex agent-based coding tasks and search operations. Available across web, iOS/Android, CLI, VS Code, and Visual Studio.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"card-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"tag\">IDE Integration</span>\n                        <span>📅 2026-02-15</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"quote feedback-neutral\">\n                        \"Microsoft stated Claude Sonnet 4 is optimal for Copilot, even after GPT-5's release\"\n                        <span class=\"quote-source\">- Tech report</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"card\">\n                    <div class=\"card-title\">\n                        Devin - Cognition Valuation\n                        <span class=\"badge badge-announcement\">NEWS</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"card-description\">\n                        Cognition.AI reached $10.2B valuation, highest in AI programming sector after raising $400M+. ARR grew from $1M (Sept 2024) to $73M (June 2025).\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"card-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"tag\">AI Agent</span>\n                        <span>📅 2026-02-09</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"quote feedback-positive\">\n                        \"成立两年ARR增长73倍\" (73x ARR growth in two years)\n                        <span class=\"quote-source\">- Sohu News</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"card\">\n                    <div class=\"card-title\">\n                        Codex CLI - GPT-5.2-Codex\n                        <span class=\"badge badge-feature\">FEATURE</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"card-description\">\n                        Major upgrades with GPT-5.2-Codex featuring 40% faster inference, 400K token input support, MCP protocol integration, and multi-agent parallel processing.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"card-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"tag\">CLI Tool</span>\n                        <span>📅 2026-02-09</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"card\">\n                    <div class=\"card-title\">\n                        Claude Opus 4.6\n                        <span class=\"badge badge-release\">RELEASE</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"card-description\">\n                        Anthropic's first flagship model with 1M token context window testing capabilities. Improvements in long-context querying, reasoning, and planning.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"card-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"tag\">Model</span>\n                        <span>📅 2026-02-06</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </section>\n\n            <!-- Technical Insights Section -->\n            <section class=\"technical-insights\" id=\"technical-insights\">\n                <div class=\"section-header\">\n                    <h2>💡 Technical Insights (18)</h2>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"insight-card\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/22/claude-c-compiler/\" target=\"_blank\">The Claude C Compiler</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-author\">Nicholas Carlini, Chris Lattner</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-description\">\n                        Anthropic built a C compiler using parallel Claude instances. LLVM creator Chris Lattner reviewed it as \"competent textbook implementation\" but notes AI excels at assembling known techniques while struggling with open-ended generalization.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">ai-compilers</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">open-source</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">ip-licensing</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"insight-card\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/22/raspberry-pi-stock/\" target=\"_blank\">Raspberry Pi Stock Surge</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-author\">Simon Willison</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-description\">\n                        Raspberry Pi stock spiked 30-42% amid OpenClaw excitement. CEO Eben Upton also purchased stock, halting months-long slide.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">openclaw</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">hardware</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">local-ai</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"insight-card\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/21/karpathy-claws/\" target=\"_blank\">Karpathy: 'Claws' as Next AI Layer</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-author\">Andrej Karpathy</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-description\">\n                        Defines 'Claws' as new layer on LLM agents handling orchestration, scheduling, context, tool calls, and persistence. Mentions NanoClaw (4000 LOC) and variants like zeroclaw, ironclaw, picoclaw.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">openclaw</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">agent-orchestration</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"insight-card\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://blog.google/technology/ai/gemini-3.1-pro\" target=\"_blank\">Gemini 3.1 Pro: 77.1% on ARC-AGI-2</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-author\">Google</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-description\">\n                        Released Feb 20, ranking first across 12 tests. Achieved 77.1% on ARC-AGI-2 (double previous generation). Half price of Claude Opus 4.6 at $2/$12 per million tokens.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">model-release</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">benchmarks</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"insight-card\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/20/taalas/\" target=\"_blank\">Taalas: 17,000 Tokens/Second</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-author\">Simon Willison</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-description\">\n                        Custom hardware running Llama 3.1 8B at 17,000 tokens/sec - so fast it looks like screenshot. \"Aggressively quantized, combining 3-bit and 6-bit parameters.\"\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">llm-inference</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">hardware</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"insight-card\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/20/ggml-hugging-face/\" target=\"_blank\">ggml.ai Joins Hugging Face</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-author\">Georgi Gerganov</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-description\">\n                        Creator of llama.cpp joining Hugging Face. Plan to integrate GGML with Transformers and improve local model UX. Kicked off local model movement in March 2023.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">local-llms</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">open-source</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"insight-card\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/20/prompt-caching/\" target=\"_blank\">Prompt Caching Enables Agents</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-author\">Thariq Shihipar (Anthropic)</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-description\">\n                        Claude Code built around prompt caching. High cache hit rates decrease costs and enable generous rate limits. Team runs alerts on cache hit rates and declares SEVs if too low.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">prompt-caching</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">cost-optimization</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"insight-card\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/18/type-hints/\" target=\"_blank\">Coming Around to Type Hints</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-author\">Simon Willison</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-description\">\n                        After resisting for 25+ years, now prefers type hints because coding agents do the typing. Benefits of explicit types without iteration speed penalty.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">static-typing</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">ai-assisted-programming</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"insight-card\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/18/paul-ford-nyt/\" target=\"_blank\">Paul Ford: AI Disruption Arrived</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-author\">Paul Ford (NYT)</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-description\">\n                        November moment when AI coding tools suddenly got much better. Examples: completing $25K and $350K projects for $200/month Claude plan. \"All the people I love hate this stuff.\"\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">ai-assisted-programming</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">careers</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"insight-card\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/18/martin-fowler/\" target=\"_blank\">Martin Fowler on LLMs Eating Skills</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-author\">Martin Fowler</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-description\">\n                        \"LLMs are eating specialty skills. Less use of specialist front-end and back-end developers as LLM-driving skills become more important.\" Rise of Expert Generalists?\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">careers</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">llm-impact</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"insight-card\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/17/claude-sonnet-4.6/\" target=\"_blank\">Claude Sonnet 4.6 Released</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-author\">Anthropic</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-description\">\n                        Performance similar to Opus 4.5 but at Sonnet pricing ($3/$15 vs $5/$25). Knowledge cutoff Aug 2025. Apparently loves adding top hats to pelicans in SVG tests.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">llm-release</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">pricing</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"insight-card\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://dentro.de/ai/news/\" target=\"_blank\">OpenClaw: 200K+ GitHub Stars</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-author\">Peter Steinberger</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-description\">\n                        Self-hostable AI execution engine with OS-level access. Feb 17 version released with Sonnet 4.6 integration, 1M context testing, iOS share extension.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">openclaw</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">autonomous-agents</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"insight-card\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://juejin.cn/post/7607358297457278976\" target=\"_blank\">Peter Steinberger Joins OpenAI</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-author\">TechMedia</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-description\">\n                        OpenClaw creator joined OpenAI Feb 14. Project transitioning to independent foundation. Sparked Mac mini buying frenzy and derivatives like ZeroClaw (99% lower memory).\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">openclaw</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">acquisition</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"insight-card\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://developer.aliyun.com/article/1712671\" target=\"_blank\">Kimi Claw: Zero-Deployment OpenClaw</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-author\">Moonshot AI</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-description\">\n                        Browser-based, zero-deployment OpenClaw powered by Kimi K2.5 model. Company raised $700M from Alibaba/Tencent, valuation doubled to exceed $10B.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">openclaw</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">ai-in-china</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"insight-card\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/html/2602.16741v1\" target=\"_blank\">LLM Code Reviewers Research</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-author\">ArXiv Paper</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-description\">\n                        Study shows LLM reviewers more robust than expected at detecting vulnerability patterns, though adversarial comments can confuse them. Important for AI-assisted code review reliability.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">llm-code-review</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">security</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"insight-card\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/@TwoMinutePapers\" target=\"_blank\">Gemini 3.1 Pro Video Review</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-author\">Two Minute Papers</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-description\">\n                        Video gained 1M+ views in 1 hour. Demonstrates model capabilities, compares against GPT-5.2, covers scenarios where it outperformed competitors.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">ai-education</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">benchmarks</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"insight-card\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://github.com/DataExpert-io/ai-engineer-handbook\" target=\"_blank\">AI Engineer Handbook 2026</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-author\">DataExpert-io</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-description\">\n                        Compiles essential resources including 3Blue1Brown (6M+), Yannic Kilcher (250K+), Two Minute Papers (1.5M+), AI Explained (500K+). Curated knowledge map for AI engineering careers.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">ai-engineering</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">education</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"insight-card\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/19/swe-bench/\" target=\"_blank\">SWE-bench February Update</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-author\">Simon Willison</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-description\">\n                        Fresh results testing models against 500 verified coding problems. Claude 4.5 Opus leads at 76.8%, followed by Gemini 3 Flash (75.8%). Chinese models comprise 40% of top 10.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">benchmarks</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic-tag\">coding-agents</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </section>\n        </div>\n    </main>\n\n    <footer>\n        <div class=\"footer-links\">\n            <a href=\"#\">About Agent Daily</a>\n            <a href=\"#\">Methodology</a>\n            <a href=\"#\">Submit Product</a>\n            <a href=\"#\">RSS Feed</a>\n            <a href=\"#\">Twitter</a>\n        </div>\n        <p>\n            <strong>Agent Daily Report</strong> - Generated on February 24, 2026<br>\n            Powered by Claude Agent SDK | Tracking agentic coding tools and AI development platforms<br>\n            Data compiled from public sources, community feedback, and industry research\n        </p>\n        <p class=\"mt-10\">\n            <em>Report covers period: February 6-24, 2026</em>\n        </p>\n    </footer>\n</body>\n</html>"
