rgin-top: 5px;\n   130→        }\n   131→\n   132→        .update-type {\n   133→            font-size: 10px;\n   134→            text-transform: uppercase;\n   135→            font-weight: bold;\n   136→            color: #ff6600;\n   137→            margin-bottom: 3px;\n   138→        }\n   139→\n   140→        .feedback {\n   141→            margin-top: 8px;\n   142→            padding-left: 10px;\n   143→            border-left: 2px solid #d4d4d4;\n   144→            font-size: 11px;\n   145→            color: #828282;\n   146→        }\n   147→\n   148→        .feedback-quote {\n   149→            font-style: italic;\n   150→            margin-bottom: 4px;\n   151→        }\n   152→\n   153→        .feedback-source {\n   154→            font-size: 10px;\n   155→            color: #999999;\n   156→        }\n   157→\n   158→        footer {\n   159→            margin-top: 20px;\n   160→            padding: 10px;\n   161→            text-align: center;\n   162→            font-size: 11px;\n   163→            color: #828282;\n   164→            border-top: 1px solid #d4d4d4;\n   165→        }\n   166→\n   167→        footer a {\n   168→            color: #828282;\n   169→            text-decoration: none;\n   170→        }\n   171→\n   172→        footer a:hover {\n   173→            text-decoration: underline;\n   174→        }\n   175→\n   176→        .topics {\n   177→            margin-top: 5px;\n   178→        }\n   179→\n   180→        .topic {\n   181→            display: inline-block;\n   182→            font-size: 10px;\n   183→            color: #666666;\n   184→            margin-right: 5px;\n   185→            margin-bottom: 2px;\n   186→        }\n   187→\n   188→        @media print {\n   189→            body {\n   190→                background-color: #ffffff;\n   191→            }\n   192→\n   193→            section {\n   194→                border: none;\n   195→                page-break-inside: avoid;\n   196→            }\n   197→\n   198→            .three-column-layout {\n   199→                display: block;\n   200→            }\n   201→\n   202→            section {\n   203→                margin-bottom: 20px;\n   204→                page-break-inside: avoid;\n   205→            }\n   206→        }\n   207→\n   208→        .source-link {\n   209→            color: #828282;\n   210→            font-size: 10px;\n   211→        }\n   212→\n   213→        .highlight {\n   214→            background-color: #ffffd0;\n   215→            padding: 2px 4px;\n   216→        }\n   217→    </style>\n   218→</head>\n   219→<body>\n   220→    <div class=\"container\">\n   221→        <header>\n   222→            <h1>Agentic Coding Research Report</h1>\n   223→            <div class=\"date\">February 24, 2026</div>\n   224→        </header>\n   225→\n   226→        <main class=\"three-column-layout\">\n   227→            <!-- Left Column: New Products -->\n   228→            <section class=\"new-products\">\n   229→                <h2>New Products & Tools</h2>\n   230→\n   231→                <div class=\"item\">\n   232→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   233→                        <a href=\"https://www.jetbrains.com/ai/\">Junie (JetBrains AI Coding Agent)</a>\n   234→                    </div>\n   235→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   236→                        AI coding agent from JetBrains that executes complex tasks and provides fine-grained control for human-computer interaction in JetBrains IDEs. Now publicly available to all JetBrains customers.\n   237→                    </div>\n   238→                    <div class=\"meta\">\n   239→                        <span>📅 2026-02-19</span>\n   240→                        <span>🔧 IDE-integrated</span>\n   241→                    </div>\n   242→                    <div class=\"tag\">AI coding agent</div>\n   243→                </div>\n   244→\n   245→                <div class=\"item\">\n   246→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   247→                        <a href=\"https://www.jetbrains.com/ai/\">JetBrains AI Free Tier</a>\n   248→                    </div>\n   249→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   250→                        New free tier offering unlimited code completion, access to local AI models, and credit-based cloud AI assistance with 30 days of AI Pro access. All JetBrains AI tools now available through single subscription.\n   251→                    </div>\n   252→                    <div class=\"meta\">\n   253→                        <span>📅 2026-02-19</span>\n   254→                        <span>💰 Free tier</span>\n   255→                    </div>\n   256→                    <div class=\"tag\">IDE-integrated AI tool</div>\n   257→                </div>\n   258→\n   259→                <div class=\"item\">\n   260→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   261→                        <a href=\"https://codeium.com/windsurf\">Windsurf Wave 13</a>\n   262→                    </div>\n   263→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   264→                        Latest release with multi-agent workflow upgrades, performance enhancements, accessibility improvements, and terminal reliability improvements.\n   265→                    </div>\n   266→                    <div class=\"meta\">\n   267→                        <span>📅 2026-02-25</span>\n   268→                        <span>⚡ Performance</span>\n   269→                    </div>\n   270→                    <div class=\"tag\">AI IDE</div>\n   271→                </div>\n   272→\n   273→                <div class=\"item\">\n   274→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   275→                        <a href=\"https://claude.ai/code\">Claude Code Security Module</a>\n   276→                    </div>\n   277→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   278→                        Combines automated scanning with human-like analysis to identify business logic defects, access control issues, and security vulnerabilities. Uses multi-stage verification to filter false positives.\n   279→                    </div>\n   280→                    <div class=\"meta\">\n   281→                        <span>📅 2026-02-20</span>\n   282→                        <span>🔒 Security</span>\n   283→                    </div>\n   284→                    <div class=\"tag\">Security tool</div>\n   285→                </div>\n   286→\n   287→                <div class=\"item\">\n   288→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   289→                        <a href=\"https://geminicli.com/docs/changelogs/\">Gemini CLI v0.29.0</a>\n   290→                    </div>\n   291→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   292→                        Weekly update with support for Gemini 3 Pro and Flash models with enhanced reasoning and coding capabilities.\n   293→                    </div>\n   294→                    <div class=\"meta\">\n   295→                        <span>📅 2026-02-19</span>\n   296→                        <span>💻 CLI</span>\n   297→                    </div>\n   298→                    <div class=\"tag\">Developer tool</div>\n   299→                </div>\n   300→\n   301→                <div class=\"item\">\n   302→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   303→                        <a href=\"https://github.com/features/copilot\">GitHub Copilot + Claude Sonnet 4.6</a>\n   304→                    </div>\n   305→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   306→                        GitHub Copilot integrated Anthropic's Claude Sonnet 4.6 model, excelling at complex agent-based coding tasks and search operations. Available across web, mobile, CLI, and IDEs.\n   307→                    </div>\n   308→                    <div class=\"meta\">\n   309→                        <span>📅 2026-02-15</span>\n   310→                        <span>🤖 Integration</span>\n   311→                    </div>\n   312→                    <div class=\"tag\">Multi-model platform</div>\n   313→                </div>\n   314→            </section>\n   315→\n   316→            <!-- Middle Column: Whitelist Updates -->\n   317→            <section class=\"whitelist-updates\">\n   318→                <h2>Product Updates</h2>\n   319→\n   320→                <div class=\"item\">\n   321→                    <div class=\"update-type\">Release</div>\n   322→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   323→                        <a href=\"https://codeium.com/windsurf\">Windsurf Wave 13</a>\n   324→                    </div>\n   325→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   326→                        Multi-agent workflow upgrades, performance enhancements, accessibility improvements, and terminal reliability improvements.\n   327→                    </div>\n   328→                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-25</div>\n   329→                </div>\n   330→\n   331→                <div class=\"item\">\n   332→                    <div class=\"update-type\">Feature</div>\n   333→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   334→                        <a href=\"https://claude.ai/code\">Claude Code Security Module</a>\n   335→                    </div>\n   336→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   337→                        Automated scanning with human-like analysis to identify business logic defects, access control issues, and security vulnerabilities with severity ratings.\n   338→                    </div>\n   339→                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-20</div>\n   340→                    <div class=\"feedback\">\n   341→                        <div class=\"feedback-quote\">\"AI杀到！Claude代码安全工具问世，全球网安股遭'血洗'\"</div>\n   342→                        <div class=\"feedback-source\">CSDN Blog</div>\n   343→                    </div>\n   344→                    <div class=\"feedback\">\n   345→                        <div class=\"feedback-quote\">\"Cybersecurity stocks crashed: sector market cap evaporated by over $10 billion\"</div>\n   346→                        <div class=\"feedback-source\">Multiple news reports</div>\n   347→                    </div>\n   348→                </div>\n   349→\n   350→                <div class=\"item\">\n   351→                    <div class=\"update-type\">Feature</div>\n   352→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   353→                        <a href=\"https://geminicli.com/docs/changelogs/\">Google DeepMind Lyria 3 Integration</a>\n   354→                    </div>\n   355→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   356→                        Lyria 3 music generation model now available in Gemini, expanding the CLI's multimodal capabilities.\n   357→                    </div>\n   358→                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-19</div>\n   359→                </div>\n   360→\n   361→                <div class=\"item\">\n   362→                    <div class=\"update-type\">Announcement</div>\n   363→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   364→                        <a href=\"https://devin.ai\">Devin - $10.2B Valuation</a>\n   365→                    </div>\n   366→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   367→                        Cognition.AI reached $10.2 billion valuation after raising $400M. ARR grew from $1M (Sept 2024) to $73M (June 2025).\n   368→                    </div>\n   369→                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-09</div>\n   370→                    <div class=\"feedback\">\n   371→                        <div class=\"feedback-quote\">\"成立两年ARR增长73倍，AI编程Cognition AI估值突破100亿美元\"</div>\n   372→                        <div class=\"feedback-source\">Sohu News</div>\n   373→                    </div>\n   374→                </div>\n   375→\n   376→                <div class=\"item\">\n   377→                    <div class=\"update-type\">Release</div>\n   378→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   379→                        <a href=\"https://claude.ai/code\">Claude Opus 4.6</a>\n   380→                    </div>\n   381→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   382→                        First flagship model with 1 million token context window testing capabilities, with improvements in long-context querying, reasoning, and planning.\n   383→                    </div>\n   384→                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-06</div>\n   385→                </div>\n   386→\n   387→                <div class=\"item\">\n   388→                    <div class=\"update-type\">Feature</div>\n   389→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   390→                        <a href=\"https://github.com/features/copilot\">Copilot + Claude Sonnet 4.6</a>\n   391→                    </div>\n   392→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   393→                        Integrated Anthropic's Claude Sonnet 4.6 model for complex agent-based coding tasks and search operations across all platforms.\n   394→                    </div>\n   395→                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-15</div>\n   396→                    <div class=\"feedback\">\n   397→                        <div class=\"feedback-quote\">\"GitHub把OpenAI当备胎，Copilot接入Claude+Gemini\"</div>\n   398→                        <div class=\"feedback-source\">Social media discussions</div>\n   399→                    </div>\n   400→                </div>\n   401→\n   402→                <div class=\"item\">\n   403→                    <div class=\"update-type\">Release</div>\n   404→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   405→                        <a href=\"https://geminicli.com/docs/changelogs/\">Gemini CLI v0.29.0</a>\n   406→                    </div>\n   407→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   408→                        Weekly update supporting Gemini 3 Pro and Flash models with enhanced reasoning and coding capabilities.\n   409→                    </div>\n   410→                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-19</div>\n   411→                </div>\n   412→            </section>\n   413→\n   414→            <!-- Right Column: Technical Insights -->\n   415→            <section class=\"technical-insights\">\n   416→                <h2>Technical Insights</h2>\n   417→\n   418→                <div class=\"item\">\n   419→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   420→                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/22/claude-c-compiler/\">The Claude C Compiler</a>\n   421→                    </div>\n   422→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   423→                        Anthropic's Nicholas Carlini built a C compiler using parallel Claude instances. Chris Lattner (LLVM creator) notes it looks like a 'competent textbook implementation' but highlights AI excels at assembling known techniques.\n   424→                    </div>\n   425→                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-22</div>\n   426→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   427→                        <span class=\"topic\">#ai-compilers</span>\n   428→                        <span class=\"topic\">#anthropic</span>\n   429→                        <span class=\"topic\">#open-source</span>\n   430→                    </div>\n   431→                </div>\n   432→\n   433→                <div class=\"item\">\n   434→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   435→                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/22/raspberry-pi-stock/\">Raspberry Pi Stock Surges</a>\n   436→                    </div>\n   437→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   438→                        Stock spiked 30-42% amid excitement about OpenClaw viral AI personal assistant running on Raspberry Pi hardware.\n   439→                    </div>\n   440→                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-22</div>\n   441→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   442→                        <span class=\"topic\">#openclaw</span>\n   443→                        <span class=\"topic\">#hardware</span>\n   444→                    </div>\n   445→                </div>\n   446→\n   447→                <div class=\"item\">\n   448→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   449→                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/21/karpathy-claws/\">Karpathy on 'Claws'</a>\n   450→                    </div>\n   451→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   452→                        Andrej Karpathy defines 'Claws' as new layer on top of LLM agents handling orchestration, scheduling, context, tool calls, and persistence.\n   453→                    </div>\n   454→                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-21</div>\n   455→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   456→                        <span class=\"topic\">#andrej-karpathy</span>\n   457→                        <span class=\"topic\">#agent-orchestration</span>\n   458→                    </div>\n   459→                </div>\n   460→\n   461→                <div class=\"item\">\n   462→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   463→                        <a href=\"https://blog.google/technology/ai/gemini-3.1-pro\">Gemini 3.1 Pro - 77.1% ARC-AGI-2</a>\n   464→                    </div>\n   465→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   466→                        Achieved 77.1% on ARC-AGI-2 benchmark (double previous generation). Half the price of Claude Opus 4.6 at $2/$12 per million tokens.\n   467→                    </div>\n   468→                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-20</div>\n   469→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   470→                        <span class=\"topic\">#benchmarks</span>\n   471→                        <span class=\"topic\">#pricing</span>\n   472→                    </div>\n   473→                </div>\n   474→\n   475→                <div class=\"item\">\n   476→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   477→                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/20/taalas/\">Taalas: 17,000 Tokens/Second</a>\n   478→                    </div>\n   479→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   480→                        Custom hardware implementation of Llama 3.1 8B running at 17,000 tokens/second - so fast it looks like a screenshot.\n   481→                    </div>\n   482→                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-20</div>\n   483→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   484→                        <span class=\"topic\">#llm-inference</span>\n   485→                        <span class=\"topic\">#hardware</span>\n   486→                    </div>\n   487→                </div>\n   488→\n   489→                <div class=\"item\">\n   490→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   491→                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/20/ggml-hugging-face/\">ggml.ai Joins Hugging Face</a>\n   492→                    </div>\n   493→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   494→                        Georgi Gerganov's ggml.ai (creator of llama.cpp) is joining Hugging Face to ensure long-term progress of local AI.\n   495→                    </div>\n   496→                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-20</div>\n   497→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   498→                        <span class=\"topic\">#local-llms</span>\n   499→                        <span class=\"topic\">#open-source</span>\n   500→                    </div>\n   501→                </div>\n   502→\n   503→                <div class=\"item\">\n   504→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   505→                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/20/prompt-caching/\">Prompt Caching Insights</a>\n   506→                    </div>\n   507→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   508→                        Claude Code builds entire harness around prompt caching. High cache hit rates decrease costs and enable more generous rate limits.\n   509→                    </div>\n   510→                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-20</div>\n   511→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   512→                        <span class=\"topic\">#prompt-caching</span>\n   513→                        <span class=\"topic\">#cost-optimization</span>\n   514→                    </div>\n   515→                </div>\n   516→\n   517→                <div class=\"item\">\n   518→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   519→                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/19/swe-bench/\">SWE-bench Update</a>\n   520→                    </div>\n   521→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   522→                        Claude 4.5 Opus leads at 76.8%, followed by Gemini 3 Flash (75.8%). Chinese models comprise 40% of top 10.\n   523→                    </div>\n   524→                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-19</div>\n   525→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   526→                        <span class=\"topic\">#benchmarks</span>\n   527→                        <span class=\"topic\">#coding-agents</span>\n   528→                    </div>\n   529→                </div>\n   530→\n   531→                <div class=\"item\">\n   532→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   533→                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/18/type-hints/\">Coming Around to Type Hints</a>\n   534→                    </div>\n   535→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   536→                        Simon Willison: Now preferring type hints after 25+ years of resistance because coding agents do the typing.\n   537→                    </div>\n   538→                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-18</div>\n   539→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   540→                        <span class=\"topic\">#programming-languages</span>\n   541→                        <span class=\"topic\">#static-typing</span>\n   542→                    </div>\n   543→                </div>\n   544→\n   545→                <div class=\"item\">\n   546→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   547→                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/18/paul-ford-nyt/\">Paul Ford: AI Disruption Arrived</a>\n   548→                    </div>\n   549→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   550→                        NYT opinion: AI coding tools suddenly got much better. Examples of completing $25,000 and $350,000 projects for $200/month Claude plan.\n   551→                    </div>\n   552→                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-18</div>\n   553→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   554→                        <span class=\"topic\">#ai-assisted-programming</span>\n   555→                        <span class=\"topic\">#careers</span>\n   556→                    </div>\n   557→                </div>\n   558→\n   559→                <div class=\"item\">\n   560→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   561→                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/17/claude-sonnet-4.6/\">Claude Sonnet 4.6 Released</a>\n   562→                    </div>\n   563→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   564→                        Performance similar to Opus 4.5 but at Sonnet pricing ($3/$15 vs $5/$25 per million tokens). Knowledge cutoff: August 2025.\n   565→                    </div>\n   566→                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-17</div>\n   567→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   568→                        <span class=\"topic\">#anthropic</span>\n   569→                        <span class=\"topic\">#pricing</span>\n   570→                    </div>\n   571→                </div>\n   572→\n   573→                <div class=\"item\">\n   574→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   575→                        <a href=\"https://dentro.de/ai/news/\">OpenClaw: The AI That Does Things</a>\n   576→                    </div>\n   577→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   578→                        Self-hostable AI execution engine with 200,000+ GitHub stars. Can execute tasks autonomously with OS-level access.\n   579→                    </div>\n   580→                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-17</div>\n   581→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   582→                        <span class=\"topic\">#openclaw</span>\n   583→                        <span class=\"topic\">#autonomous-agents</span>\n   584→                    </div>\n   585→                </div>\n   586→\n   587→                <div class=\"item\">\n   588→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   589→                        <a href=\"https://juejin.cn/post/7607358297457278976\">Peter Steinberger Joins OpenAI</a>\n   590→                    </div>\n   591→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   592→                        OpenClaw creator joined OpenAI on February 14, 2026. OpenClaw transitioning to independent foundation. Sparked Mac mini buying frenzy.\n   593→                    </div>\n   594→                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-17</div>\n   595→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   596→                        <span class=\"topic\">#openclaw</span>\n   597→                        <span class=\"topic\">#openai</span>\n   598→                    </div>\n   599→                </div>\n   600→\n   601→                <div class=\"item\">\n   602→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   603→                        <a href=\"https://developer.aliyun.com/article/1712671\">Kimi Claw - Zero-Deployment OpenClaw</a>\n   604→                    </div>\n   605→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   606→                        Moonshot AI launched browser-based, zero-deployment OpenClaw powered by Kimi K2.5 model. Company raised $700M, valuation >$10B.\n   607→                    </div>\n   608→                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-17</div>\n   609→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   610→                        <span class=\"topic\">#openclaw</span>\n   611→                        <span class=\"topic\">#ai-in-china</span>\n   612→                    </div>\n   613→                </div>\n   614→\n   615→                <div class=\"item\">\n   616→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   617→                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/18/martin-fowler/\">Martin Fowler on LLMs</a>\n   618→                    </div>\n   619→                    <div class=\"description\">\n   620→                        \"LLMs are eating specialty skills. There will be less use of specialist front-end and back-end developers.\"\n   621→                    </div>\n   622→                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-18</div>\n   623→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   624→                        <span class=\"topic\">#careers</span>\n   625→                        <span class=\"topic\">#llm-impact</span>\n   626→                    </div>\n   627→                </div>\n   628→            </section>\n   629→        </main>\n   630→\n   631→        <footer>\n   632→            <a href=\"#\">Top</a> |\n   633→            <a href=\"#\">About</a> |\n   634→            <a href=\"#\">Archive</a> |\n   635→            <a href=\"#\">RSS</a>\n   636→            <div style=\"margin-top: 10px;\">\n   637→                Generated with Claude Code | Research data compiled: 2026-02-24\n   638→            </div>\n   639→        </footer>\n   640→    </div>\n   641→</body>\n   642→</html>\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"
