6-02-22</div>\n                    <div class=\"topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic\">#ai-compilers</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">#anthropic</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">#open-source</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/22/raspberry-pi-stock/\">Raspberry Pi Stock Surges</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"description\">\n                        Stock spiked 30-42% amid excitement about OpenClaw viral AI personal assistant running on Raspberry Pi hardware.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-22</div>\n                    <div class=\"topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic\">#openclaw</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">#hardware</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/21/karpathy-claws/\">Karpathy on 'Claws'</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"description\">\n                        Andrej Karpathy defines 'Claws' as new layer on top of LLM agents handling orchestration, scheduling, context, tool calls, and persistence.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-21</div>\n                    <div class=\"topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic\">#andrej-karpathy</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">#agent-orchestration</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://blog.google/technology/ai/gemini-3.1-pro\">Gemini 3.1 Pro - 77.1% ARC-AGI-2</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"description\">\n                        Achieved 77.1% on ARC-AGI-2 benchmark (double previous generation). Half the price of Claude Opus 4.6 at $2/$12 per million tokens.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-20</div>\n                    <div class=\"topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic\">#benchmarks</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">#pricing</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/20/taalas/\">Taalas: 17,000 Tokens/Second</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"description\">\n                        Custom hardware implementation of Llama 3.1 8B running at 17,000 tokens/second - so fast it looks like a screenshot.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-20</div>\n                    <div class=\"topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic\">#llm-inference</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">#hardware</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/20/ggml-hugging-face/\">ggml.ai Joins Hugging Face</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"description\">\n                        Georgi Gerganov's ggml.ai (creator of llama.cpp) is joining Hugging Face to ensure long-term progress of local AI.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"meta\">2026-02-20</div>\n                    <div class=\"topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic\">#local-llms</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">#open-source